			<p style="font-size:14pt">GDOC Publication Policy</p>
				<p>
				Prior to the publication of a scientific journal article describing G-DOC, researchers using G-DOC are
				requested to include the following acknowledgment in any publication or presentation:</p>
				
				<blockquote style="width:400px;text-wrap:suppress;margin-left:22%">
				The data/analytic tools utilized in this study were provided by the Georgetown Database of
				Cancer (G-DOC), an internally funded project of the Lombardi Comprehensive Cancer Center
				designed to provide advanced translational research tools to the scientific community.</blockquote>

				<p>
				This statement will be modified upon publication of the first G-DOC paper in 2011.</p>
				
				<p>
				Copies of all publications and presentations using G-DOC tools and/or data should be provided to the
				G-DOC team using the “Contact Us” link, or by sending them directly to <a href="mailto:gdoc-help@georgetown.edu?subject=Feedback for G-DOC application">gdoc-help@georgetown.edu</a>
				G-DOC will issue periodic updates on its Web site and in other publications regarding the status
				of successful research projects that use its tools and/or data. These updates may include contact
				information for the Principal Investigator.
			</p>
